# ğŸ§± Libft â€“ My Custom C Standard Library

## ğŸ“š What is Libft?

Libft is the very first project in the 42 School curriculum. The goal is to **recreate several standard C library functions** from scratch â€” without using any of the built-in C library functions (except `write`, `malloc`, and `free` in some cases).

This project helps students understand:
- Memory manipulation
- String operations
- Character checks
- Linked list data structures
- How the C Standard Library works under the hood

It is the foundation for almost every future project at 42.

---

## ğŸš€ Project Structure

### Part 1 â€“ Libc Functions
Rewriting common standard C functions:
- `ft_memset`, `ft_bzero`, `ft_memcpy`, `ft_memmove`
- `ft_strlcpy`, `ft_strlcat`, `ft_strlen`, `ft_strchr`, `ft_strrchr`
- `ft_strncmp`, `ft_memchr`, `ft_memcmp`, `ft_strnstr`
- `ft_atoi`, `ft_isalpha`, `ft_isdigit`, `ft_isalnum`, `ft_isascii`, `ft_isprint`
- `ft_toupper`, `ft_tolower`
- `ft_calloc`, `ft_strdup`

### Part 2 â€“ Additional Functions
Creating more complex functions:
- `ft_substr`, `ft_strjoin`, `ft_strtrim`
- `ft_split`, `ft_itoa`, `ft_strmapi`, `ft_striteri`
- `ft_putchar_fd`, `ft_putstr_fd`, `ft_putendl_fd`, `ft_putnbr_fd`

### Bonus Part â€“ Linked Lists
Implementing a custom singly linked list library:
- `ft_lstnew`, `ft_lstadd_front`, `ft_lstsize`, `ft_lstlast`
- `ft_lstadd_back`, `ft_lstdelone`, `ft_lstclear`, `ft_lstiter`, `ft_lstmap`

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ How to Compile

```bash
make        # Compiles libft.a
make clean  # Removes object files
make fclean # Removes object files and the library
make re     # Recompiles everything from scratch



